review_blob: I recently tried this beer as an obligation for living in San Diego and loving beer. The appearance and aroma were above average, but the taste was great. Rarely do I immediatley fall for a Pale Ale without numerous tastes and time, but this got me hooked.This is a good medium bodied Pale with  little head and a slightly sweet malt flavor. It goes down full of flavor and finishes crisp.

My impression of this beer was good. I am a fan of good micro-brewed honey ales, and this impressed me. I pours with little head, but a nich golden color. Upon first taste, you will immediatley notice a sweet honey toasted flavor. Its rich, but not too much to handle. I finished clean and crisp. The is a lighter bodied beer which goes perfect with one of the brewerys fine cuisines.
beer_name: San Marcos Wild Clover Honey Ale

review_blob: Nice rich, full bodied ale. When the beer first him my mouth, I could immediatley taste a slightly sweet malt flavor. As the beer continues down the throat, the beer becomes increasingly smooth, sweet, and ends with a clean, pleasant aftertaste. You can definitley tell this beer is higher in the alcohol content.
